            The formula for a circle's circumference is <m>c=\pi d</m>,
            where <m>c</m> represents circumference, <m>d</m> represents diameter,
            and <m>\pi</m> is a constant with the value of <m>3.1415926\ldots</m>.
            Use the given circumference to write an equation
            that could be used to find that circle's diameter.
            Then find the diameter.
          </p>
        </introduction>

        <exercise label="find-diameter">
          <webwork xml:id="webwork-find-diameter">
